.TH F00-SHA256SUM 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.9" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-sha256sum \- compute and check SHA256 message digest (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-sha256sum
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print or check SHA256 (256\-bit) checksums.
With no FILE, or when FILE is \-, read standard input.
Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU sha256sum\-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-binary\fR
read in binary mode
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-check\fR
read checksums from the FILEs and check them
.TP
\fB\-\-tag\fR
create a BSD\-style checksum
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-text\fR
read in text mode (default)
.TP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-warn\fR
warn about improperly formatted checksum lines
.PP
See
.B f00\-sha256sum \-\-help
for the full flag list.
Related:
.BR f00\-md5sum ,
.BR f00\-sha1sum ,
.BR f00\-sha512sum ,
.BR f00\-b2sum .
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON digest summary
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV digest summary
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sha256sum (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
